parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure - Fuel Leaking from Fuel Line
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaking from the fuel line can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to serious accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel spraying from the fuel line
fuel leaking from the motorcycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect - Delayed Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed availability of parts for the recall repair can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available for repair
dealer confirms parts are not yet available
manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump High Pressure Fitting Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump high pressure fitting can cause a major fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially when fuel drips onto the hot exhaust pipe or engine. This can result in serious injury or even death.
symptoms: Fuel leak from the high pressure fitting on the fuel pump
fuel dripping onto the hot exhaust pipe or engine
fuel pooling on top of the fuel pump
risk of fire
possibility of fuel getting on the rider's pant leg and causing burns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the throttle cable bell cranks/cams due to poor quality plastic material can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially when entering traffic, turning, or traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
engine returns to idle RPM
hand throttle no longer works.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the engine stalls or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the fuel pump leaks fuel
the fuel pump overflows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause the brakes to seize or drag, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brakes feel spongy or soft
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise
the brakes vibrate or pulse
the brakes overheat
the brake caliper seizes or drags.
